==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek [[φάρμακεία]] (pharmakeia), "the use of drugs", and [[φάρμακον]] (pharmakon), "a drug, charm, enchantment", via middle Latin [[pharmacia]]. Ultimately from ancient Greek [[φαρμακίς]] (pharmakis), "[[witch]]".

===Noun===
'''pharmacy'''

#a place where [[prescription]] drugs are [[dispensed]], a [[dispensary]]
#the practice of dispensing such drugs
#the occupation of a [[pharmacist]]

